    correction: "**Limite en $+\\infty$ :** Pour $x > 0$, $\\sqrt{x^2+1} = x\\sqrt{1+\\frac{1}{x^2}}$.\n\n$f(x) = \\dfrac{x\\sqrt{1+\\frac{1}{x^2}}}{x+2} = \\dfrac{\\sqrt{1+\\frac{1}{x^2}}}{1+\\frac{2}{x}} \\xrightarrow[x\\to+\\infty]{} \\dfrac{1}{1} = \\boxed{1}$\n\nAsymptote horizontale $y = 1$ en $+\\infty$.\n\n**Limite en $-\\infty$ :** Pour $x < 0$, $\\sqrt{x^2+1} = |x|\\sqrt{1+\\frac{1}{x^2}} = -x\\sqrt{1+\\frac{1}{x^2}}$ (car $|x| = -x$).\n\n$f(x) = \\dfrac{-x\\sqrt{1+\\frac{1}{x^2}}}{x+2} = \\dfrac{-\\sqrt{1+\\frac{1}{x^2}}}{1+\\frac{2}{x}} \\xrightarrow[x\\to-\\infty]{} \\dfrac{-1}{1} = \\boxed{-1}$\n\nAsymptote horizontale $y = -1$ en $-\\infty$."
