      statement: 'Calculer $\\displaystyle\\lim_{x \\to 0} \\frac{1 - \\cos x}{x}$.',
      correction: '$\\dfrac{1 - \\cos x}{x} = \\dfrac{1 - \\cos x}{x^2} \\times x$\n\nOr $\\displaystyle\\lim_{x \\to 0} \\dfrac{1 - \\cos x}{x^2} = \\dfrac{1}{2}$ (limite connue) et $\\displaystyle\\lim_{x \\to 0} x = 0$.\n\nDonc $\\displaystyle\\lim_{x \\to 0} \\dfrac{1 - \\cos x}{x} = \\dfrac{1}{2} \\times 0 = 0$.'
    },
