      correction: '**Développement de la forme proposée :**\n$\\sqrt{2}\\sin\\left(x + \\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\right) = \\sqrt{2}\\left[\\sin x \\cos\\dfrac{\\pi}{4} + \\cos x \\sin\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\right]$\n$= \\sqrt{2}\\left[\\sin x \\cdot \\dfrac{\\sqrt{2}}{2} + \\cos x \\cdot \\dfrac{\\sqrt{2}}{2}\\right] = \\sin x + \\cos x = f(x)$ ✓\n\n**Extrema :**\n$f(x) = \\sqrt{2}\\sin\\left(x + \\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\right)$\n- Maximum : $\\sqrt{2}$, atteint quand $x + \\dfrac{\\pi}{4} = \\dfrac{\\pi}{2} + 2k\\pi$, soit $x = \\dfrac{\\pi}{4} + 2k\\pi$\n- Minimum : $-\\sqrt{2}$, atteint quand $x = -\\dfrac{3\\pi}{4} + 2k\\pi$'
