    correction: "Constante de temps : $\\tau = RC = 2000 \\times 5 \\times 10^{-5} = 0{,}1\\,\\mathrm{s}$.\n\nL'équation s'écrit $u' = -\\dfrac{1}{\\tau}u + \\dfrac{E}{\\tau} = -10u + 120$.\n\n$a = -10$, solution d'équilibre $u_p = \\dfrac{120}{10} = 12\\,\\mathrm{V}$.\n\nSolution générale : $u(t) = K\\,\\mathrm{e}^{-10t} + 12$.\n\nCondition initiale : $u(0) = K + 12 = 0 \\Rightarrow K = -12$.\n\nSolution : $u(t) = 12\\left(1 - \\mathrm{e}^{-10t}\\right) = 12\\left(1 - \\mathrm{e}^{-t/\\tau}\\right)$.\n\n$u(t) = 10 \\Rightarrow 1 - \\mathrm{e}^{-10t} = \\dfrac{10}{12} = \\dfrac{5}{6} \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{e}^{-10t} = \\dfrac{1}{6} \\Rightarrow t = \\dfrac{\\ln 6}{10} \\approx 0{,}179\\,\\mathrm{s}$."
