    {
      number: 26,
      difficulty: "Difficile",
      statement: "Calculer l'aire délimitée par les courbes $f(x) = \\sin(x)$ et $g(x) = \\cos(x)$ sur $\\left[0, \\dfrac{\\pi}{2}\\right]$.",
      correction: "**Intersection :** $\\sin x = \\cos x \\Rightarrow \\tan x = 1 \\Rightarrow x = \\dfrac{\\pi}{4}$.\n\nSur $\\left[0, \\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\right]$ : $\\cos x \\geq \\sin x$. Sur $\\left[\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}, \\dfrac{\\pi}{2}\\right]$ : $\\sin x \\geq \\cos x$.\n\n$$\\mathcal{A} = \\int_0^{\\pi/4}(\\cos x - \\sin x)\\,\\mathrm{d}x + \\int_{\\pi/4}^{\\pi/2}(\\sin x - \\cos x)\\,\\mathrm{d}x$$\n$$= \\Big[\\sin x + \\cos x\\Big]_0^{\\pi/4} + \\Big[-\\cos x - \\sin x\\Big]_{\\pi/4}^{\\pi/2}$$\n$$= (\\sqrt{2}-1) + ((-1)-(-\\sqrt{2})) = (\\sqrt{2}-1)+(\\sqrt{2}-1) = 2(\\sqrt{2}-1) \\text{ u.a.}$$"
